cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper focuses on using Particle Swarm Optimization (PSO) to automatically search for the optimal architecture of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for image classification. This involves optimizing the weights and biases of the CNN layers, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper specifically focuses on image classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of PSO for optimization also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a novel encoding strategy and a Disabled layer to achieve variable-length particles, which involves designing the structure of the CNN architecture and could potentially fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
